scene.message:
Ayase: {ctl0f:1}!{nl}
Listen, Inaba just{nl}
freaked out!{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Inaba, Uesugi,{nl}
and Himeno brought back{nl}
an injured Nanjo,{nl}
and that's when...{waitkey}{nl}
And so...{nl}
{nl}

Ayase: Sonoda walked right{nl}
out of the school building,{nl}
and she's supposed{nl}
to be hospitalized!{waitkey}{nl}
Totally bizarre!{nl}
{nl}

Ms. Saeko: Inaba{nl}
came back?!{nl}
{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: ...Anyway,{nl}
Sonoda came out with them?{nl}
We have to get her back!{waitkey}

Yukino: Wait, teacher!{nl}
If something happens to you,{nl}
what about the others?{waitkey}We'll go!{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: Thanks,{nl}
Yukino!{wait_fr:32}{nl}
I owe you one.{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: Oh? {ctl0f:1},{wait_fr:32}{nl}
what are you carrying...{waitkey}{clearbox}That's...{wait_fr:32} that mask...!!{wait_fr:80}{nl}
So{wait_fr:32} it{wait_fr:16} still exists...{wait_fr:32}{nl}
a thing like that...{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: When I see{nl}
this...{wait_fr:48}{nl}
it takes me back to{nl}
high school...{waitkey}{clearbox}...It was when I{nl}
played "The Snow Queen"...{nl}
This is the mask I wore.{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: But this mask{nl}
is said to be cursed.{waitkey}{clearbox}...I know that sounds far-{nl}
fetched.{wait_fr:32}{nl}
But because of it,{nl}
my friend...{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: D-don't scare me{nl}
like that at a time{nl}
like this!{waitkey}{clearbox}That mask creeps me out.{nl}
Just throw it away!{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: Ah...{waitkey}{nl}
Oh,{wait_fr:21} sorry, sorry!{nl}
It's just an old wives'{nl}
tale — "wear it and die."{waitkey}{clearbox}But I wore it myself{nl}
and I'm totally fine,{nl}
see?{waitkey}{clearbox}So I'd be safer going{nl}
to get her back{nl}
than you would!{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: See, I've got{nl}
lady luck on my side!{wait_fr:32}{nl}
...{wait_fr:8}...{wait_fr:8}?{waitkey}{nl}
{wait_fr:16}Oh...{waitkey}{ret}

Once upon a time, there{nl}
was a very wicked demon.{waitkey}{clearbox}One day the demon made{nl}
a "mirror" — a mirror where{nl}
beautiful things looked ugly,{waitkey}and ugly things showed{nl}
up clearly.{waitkey}{clearbox}The demon tried to carry{nl}
this "devil's mirror" up{nl}
to the heavens to mock God,{waitkey}but the mirror{nl}
shattered on the way.{waitkey}{clearbox}Countless shards of the{nl}
"devil's mirror" scattered{nl}
across the earth.{wait_fr:32}{nl}
That was the beginning.{waitkey}{ret}

Once there was a boy named{nl}
Kai and a girl named Gerda{nl}
who were dear friends.{waitkey}{clearbox}One day a shard of the{nl}
"devil's mirror" entered{nl}
Kai's heart and eye.{waitkey}{clearbox}The shard made his heart{nl}
grow cold, and his eyes{nl}
could only see the bad,{waitkey}{clearbox}until even Gerda, who{nl}
loved him dearly, became{nl}
someone he only mocked.{waitkey}{ret}

On a snowy winter's day,{nl}
{waitkey}as Kai was sledding{nl}
in the square, a large{nl}
white sled appeared.{waitkey}{clearbox}Kai was carried away by{nl}
a beautiful woman{nl}
riding the white sled.{waitkey}{clearbox}That woman was none{nl}
other than the{nl}
"Snow Queen" herself!{waitkey}{clearbox}And so Kai was taken far{nl}
away to the north — to the{nl}
"Snow Queen's" ice palace.{waitkey}{ret}
